    • containsSameValues

      public static int containsSameValues​(int[] array1, int[] array2)
      Compares two int arrays and returns how many values match between the two (short) This method does NOT take into account the possibility that the same array has the same number included several times and will give a false positives if that's the case. This method was made for a personal project and only that project in mind, so its use elsewhere is not recommended and might cause unexpected issues and behaviors. (long)
      Parameters:
      array1 - Array that will be compared to array2
      array2 - Array that will be compared to array1
      Returns:
      how many numbers are shared between the two arrays

    • fillArray

      public static int[] fillArray​(int howManyNumbers, int minNumber, int maxNumber)
      Fills an int array with unique numbers asked from the user (short) you can define a range that the numbers need to be within. Method makes sure that all numbers on the array are unique(long)
      Parameters:
      howManyNumbers - how long the array should be.
      minNumber - whats the smallest the number can be
      maxNumber - whats the largest the number can be
      Returns:
      int array filled with numbers asked from the user
